HB061990.100 - 113 - XXXX 4/14/2026 3:37 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 619/VO
1 Investment Fund Advisory Committee established in KRS 164.7013;
2 (2) "Aviation" means the operation, maintenance, or manufacturing of aircraft or other
3 aerospace equipment, aerospace initiatives and efforts, and defense-related products
4 related to aerospace and aviation;
5 (3) "Aviation industry partner" means a grantor to the fund that the council determines
6 customarily employs individuals with an eligible aviation or aerospace credential in
7 a relevant aviation role in the usual course of the grantor's business;
8 (4) "Aviation program":
9 (a) Means an education or training program located in Kentucky that issues
10 eligible aviation or aerospace credentials or is a specific requirement to
11 earning an eligible aviation or aerospace credential, including but not limited
12 to a public high school vocational program; and
13 (b) Notwithstanding paragraph (a) of this subsection, does not include a flight
14 training program unless that program is a certified pilot school regulated by
15 the Federal Aviation Administration in accordance with 14 C.F.R. pt. 141, a
16 certified public postsecondary pilot school regulated by the Federal Aviation
17 Administration in accordance with 14 C.F.R. pt. 61, or is a public high
18 school vocational program;
19 (5) "Council" means the Council on Postsecondary Education;
20 (6) "Dedicated moneys" means a gift, grant, or donation to the fund that is subject to
21 restrictions imposed by a private grantor under KRS 164.7015;
22 (7) "Eligible aviation credential" means:
23 (a) Any license or certification issued by the Federal Aviation Administration;
24 (b) A Bachelor of Science in aviation issued by a postsecondary education
25 institution overseen or licensed by the council and located in Kentucky;
26 (c) Any engineering degree issued by a postsecondary education institution
27 overseen or licensed by the council and located in Kentucky; or
